:: crotch_11_crotch_10_2
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>You should be proud. Your form, your strength none of it is shameful. But pride need not be bound to flesh. Pride can live in resilience, in adaptation‚Ä¶ in what you choose to become, not just what you were born as.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>And if I don‚Äôt want to become something else?<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>Then your resistance will shape the path differently. You need not surrender instantly. But know this change has already begun. Within you, and around you. The kingdom has chosen. Your mother has chosen. The only one who hasn‚Äôt‚Ä¶ is you.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>And this‚Ä¶ potion. What exactly will it do to me?<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|crotch_11_crotch_10_3]]
<</nobr>>

:: crotch_11_crotch_10_3
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>In this first stage? Only a gentle contraction. Your‚Ä¶ current endowment will begin to reduce slowly. From what it is, to something slightly less. No pain. Just heat. Pressure. Perhaps an ache you won‚Äôt know how to describe.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>That‚Äôs still my body you‚Äôre talking about.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>Of course it is. It remains yours. Even when it changes, it belongs to you. This is not theft, Caelan it‚Äôs alchemy guided by intent. Your intent, if you will let it be.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>What if I change my mind? Or stop halfway?<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|crotch_11_crotch_10_4]]
<</nobr>>

:: crotch_11_crotch_10_4
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>Then we adjust. The process is not a prison. There is room for pause. Reassessment. Even retreat though the deeper you go, the harder it becomes to reverse. Not impossible, but costly.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>And you‚Äôve done this before? Changed others?<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>Only a few. This magic is sacred. It‚Äôs not done lightly. But each who walked the path before you found their truth some in becoming, some in choosing to remain between.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>I don‚Äôt want to lose‚Ä¶ all of me.<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|crotch_11_crotch_10_5]]
<</nobr>>

:: crotch_11_crotch_10_5
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>Then don‚Äôt. Keep what matters. Let the rest evolve. This is not about losing. It‚Äôs about crafting a shape that holds your purpose your strength as a queen, if you wish to be one.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>What happens when I drink it?<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>You‚Äôll feel a pull inward. A soft unraveling of what anchors you to maleness. Not all at once. Just a first nudge. Your body will shift slightly enough to know this is real.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>And you‚Äôll be here the whole time?<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|crotch_11_crotch_10_6]]
